305
00:21:24,520 --> 00:21:26,230
none of us will go west.

306
00:21:26,230 --> 00:21:26,840
Right?

307
00:21:26,950 --> 00:21:27,280
Yeah.

308
00:21:27,550 --> 00:21:30,000
Come on, let's toast Cheng together.

309
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:33,470
It's been a tough journey,

310
00:21:35,710 --> 00:21:36,870
but we finally made it.

311
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:38,470
What a relief!

312
00:21:39,310 --> 00:21:40,950
Yeah, such a relief.

313
00:21:40,950 --> 00:21:41,920
Couldn't agree more.

314
00:21:42,600 --> 00:21:44,070
All thanks to Cheng.

315
00:21:44,070 --> 00:21:46,200
He got us on the Jinhai "expressway".

316
00:21:46,950 --> 00:21:48,070
It saved us so much trouble.

317
00:21:50,680 --> 00:21:54,760
Cheng, we've signed
the shareholding contract.

318
00:21:55,040 --> 00:21:56,840
Why keep Wu Dengke around now?

319
00:21:57,630 --> 00:21:59,520
If Jinhai's cool with it,

320
00:21:59,950 --> 00:22:01,760
we can call a board meeting

321
00:22:02,200 --> 00:22:03,680
for electing a new chairman.

322
00:22:03,870 --> 00:22:05,520
If you become the chairman,

323
00:22:05,760 --> 00:22:06,680
the rest of us

324
00:22:06,680 --> 00:22:08,310
won't have to sneak around anymore.

325
00:22:09,520 --> 00:22:12,470
Honestly, that guy doesn't look like

326
00:22:12,840 --> 00:22:15,310
a chairman at all.

327
00:22:15,950 --> 00:22:17,070
He probably wishes

328
00:22:17,070 --> 00:22:18,390
we'd all just bring it up.

329
00:22:18,390 --> 00:22:19,040
So he can

330
00:22:19,040 --> 00:22:20,070
take a huge payout,

331
00:22:20,070 --> 00:22:21,600
and go live the easy life somewhere.

332
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:23,680
But a figurehead

333
00:22:24,360 --> 00:22:26,000
still serves a purpose.

334
00:22:27,870 --> 00:22:29,200
Right now,

335
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:31,440
it's not the time
to go head-to-head yet.

336
00:22:44,550 --> 00:22:46,470
So when do you plan to make your move?

337
00:22:54,550 --> 00:22:56,280
Mr. Wu, come here.

338
00:22:57,000 --> 00:22:57,840
It's just old friends

339
00:22:57,840 --> 00:23:00,000
having a drink together.

340
00:23:00,430 --> 00:23:01,440
Worried you wouldn't join.

341
00:23:01,630 --> 00:23:02,200
Come on.

342
00:23:02,360 --> 00:23:03,000
Take a seat.

343
00:23:03,120 --> 00:23:04,470
Listen to me, hurry up.

344
00:23:04,840 --> 00:23:06,040
Sit down.

345
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:13,790
Uncle Cheng, about the mining proposal,

346
00:23:13,900 --> 00:23:14,950
I pulled three allnighters

347
00:23:14,950 --> 00:23:15,950
and finally nailed it.

348
00:23:16,550 --> 00:23:18,120
But I couldn't find anyone to handle it.

349
00:23:18,120 --> 00:23:19,280
When I finally find someone,

350
00:23:19,280 --> 00:23:20,760
he told me

351
00:23:20,760 --> 00:23:22,390
you'd already had a meeting on it,

352
00:23:22,390 --> 00:23:23,330
and sent people to handle it.

353
00:23:27,200 --> 00:23:27,760
Mr. Wu,

354
00:23:28,350 --> 00:23:29,200
you've misunderstood.

355
00:23:29,440 --> 00:23:32,000
Look, in every major corporation,

356
00:23:32,310 --> 00:23:33,040
the chairmen

